2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0501
1 (a) As used in this section:
2
3 (i) "Diversity, equity and inclusion" includes
4 any of the following:
5
6 (A) Influencing hiring or employment
7 practices with respect to race, sex, color or ethnicity,
8 other than through the use of race and gender neutral
9 practices in accordance with any applicable state and
10 federal law;
11
12 (B) Promoting differential treatment of or
13 providing special benefits to persons on the basis of race,
14 color or ethnicity;
15
16 (C) Promoting policies or procedures
17 designed or implemented in reference to race, color or
18 ethnicity, except for policies or procedures necessary to
19 comply with any state law, federal law or applicable court
20 order;
21
22 (D) Conducting trainings, programs or
23 activities designed or implemented in reference to race,
2 SF0103

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0501
1 color, ethnicity or gender dysphonia, except for trainings,
2 programs or activities that are for the sole purpose of
3 ensuring compliance with state law, federal law or any
4 applicable court order.
5
6 (ii) "Entity" means any governmental unit,
7 special district, corporation, partnership or person that
8 will receive a legislative appropriation, directly or
9 indirectly, including agencies of the executive branch, the
10 offices of the five (5) statewide elected officials, the
11 legislature, the judiciary, community colleges, the
12 University of Wyoming, the Wyoming department of
13 transportation, the game and fish department, counties,
14 municipalities and school districts.
15
16 (b) As a condition of receiving or expending any
17 monies or funds appropriated, each entity shall not expend
18 any appropriated funds or funds received from bequests,
19 charges, deposits, donations, endowments, fees, grants,
20 gifts, tuition and any other source for programs or
21 activities that, unless federal law otherwise requires:
22
