1 (i) Establish or maintain a diversity, equity
2 and inclusion office or program;
3
4 (ii) Hire or assign an employee or a contracted
5 person to perform the duties associated with a diversity,
6 equity and inclusion office or program;
7
8 (iii) Compel, require, induce or solicit any
9 person to provide or abide by a diversity, equity and
10 inclusion statement or give preferential treatment to any
11 person based on a diversity, equity or inclusion statement;
12
13 (iv) Give preference on the basis of race, sex,
14 color, ethnicity or national origin to an applicant for
15 employment, an employee or a participant in any function of
16 the entity;
17
18 (v) Require, as a condition of employment,
19 enrollment, a contract or the receipt of funds, the
20 participation in diversity, equity and inclusion training.
21
22 (c) Nothing in this section shall be construed to:
23
