1 (i) "Constrain" means failure during any
2 semester or academic unit to provide sufficient open seats
3 in alternative courses for a student to complete or
4 progress toward completion of degree or program
5 requirements;
6
7 (ii) "Related content":
8
9 (A) Means content that does one (1) or more
10 of the following:
11
12 (I) Relates critical theory,
13 whiteness, systemic racism, institutional racism,
14 anti-racism, microaggressions, systemic bias, implicit
15 bias, unconscious bias, intersectionality, gender
16 dysphonia, social justice, cultural competence, allyship,
17 race-based reparations, race-based privilege, race-based
18 diversity, gender-based diversity, race-based equity,
19 gender-based equity, race-based inclusion or gender-based
20 inclusion to contemporary American society;
21
22 (II) Promotes the idea that racially
23 neutral or colorblind laws, policies or institutions
7 SF0103

2025 STATE OF WYOMING 25LSO-0501
1 perpetuate oppression, injustice, race-based privilege,
2 including white supremacy or white privilege, or inequity
3 by failing to actively differentiate on the basis of race,
4 sex or gender;
5
6 (III) Promotes the differential
7 treatment of any person or groups based on race or
8 ethnicity in contemporary American society;
9
10 (IV) Promotes the idea that a student
11 is biased on account of the student's race or sex.
12
13 (B) Does not include identifying and
14 discussing historical movements, ideologies or instances of
15 racial hatred or discrimination, including but not limited
16 to slavery, Indian removal, the Holocaust or
17 Japanese-American internment.
18
19 (iii) "Related course" means any course whose
20 course description, course overview, course objectives,
21 proposed student learning outcomes, written examinations or
22 written or oral assignments for which the student will
